name: test-control-center-tcc
notes: The Test Control Center (TCC) provides a consolidated facility for planning, coordinating, controlling, monitoring, and analyzing distributed test events. ,The TCC can monitor and control a test on Fort Huachuca, or other tests conducted throughout the country Primary functions of the TCC include distributed systems control and data collection and real time/near real time displays of a variety of data sources. The two control rooms can be configured or reconfigured independently. All of the terminals are connected to a dedicated local area network (LAN) and all the instrumentation is independently addressed. Content to the large overhead displays can be switched from the many sources and inputs. All of this versatility allows separate tests to be controlled simultaneously between the main and small control rooms.   TCC command and control is performed and viewed via Starship -- a test planning, command and control platform. RF modeling is performed by Orion -- our suite of electromagnetic engineering analysis tools. TCC displays include views of precision tracking and surveillance radar systems, telemetry data systems, command/control systems, video, safety, surveillance and optical tracking systems, In summary, from this location a test officer can plan, monitor, and control his test whether local, remote, or distributed; virtual, live, or constructive; developmental, operational, or a training exercise.
title: Test Control Center (TCC)
